revisions.description: Local/remote IP address, mask, gateway OIDs added
Public Release 1.22. integraBifIngressBPS, integraBifIngressPPS, integraBifEgressBPS, integraBifEgressPPS value types changed
Public Release 1.21. Radio PLL status, free physical memory, CPU idle objects added
Public Release 1.19. Ethernet QoS statistics table reworked
Public Release 1.18. Modem RMSE value type changed
Public Release 1.16. Ethernet port flow control OID added
Public Release 1.15. Ethernet statistics table updated
Public Release 1.14. System configuration executing & storing OIDs added
Public Release 1.13. Duplex shift and Tx mute OIDs are read-only. Read-write Tx mute duration OID added. Radio ranges table created
Public Release 1.12. Radio side OID is read-only. Grammar typos fixed
Public Release 1.11. Modem carrier offset OID added
Public Release 1.09. ifPortType syntax declared by IANAifType
Public Release 1.06 temperature units *10 only in description

integraBradioTxMute.name: integraBradioTxMute
integraBradioTxMute.description: Status of 'Tx mute' 1 - Tx is muted, 2 - Tx is not muted. 3 - Status information unavailable

integraBradioTxMuteDuration.name: integraBradioTxMuteDuration
integraBradioTxMuteDuration.description: Time remaning for Tx to be muted in seconds. To turn mute on send number of seconds between 10 and MAX. To turn mute off send 0. GET will retrieve remaining duration for mute or 0 if Tx mute is turned off.

integraBradioRangeEntry.name: integraBradioRangeEntry

integraBradioRangeEntryIndex.name: integraBradioRangeEntryIndex

integraBradioRangeTxPower.name: integraBradioRangeTxPower

integraBmodemAcquireStatus.name: integraBmodemAcquireStatus

integraBmodemRadialMse.name: integraBmodemRadialMse

integraBmodemFECload.name: integraBmodemFECload

integraBmodemAcquireLastStatusDetails.name: integraBmodemAcquireLastStatusDetails

integraBmodemTxCapacity.name: integraBmodemTxCapacity

integraBsysLicenseExpire.name: integraBsysLicenseExpire

integraBifPortEntry.name: integraBifPortEntry
integraBifPortEntry.description: An entry containing network physical port status info.

integraBifPortStatIndex.name: integraBifPortStatIndex
integraBifPortStatIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each physical network interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

integraBifPortStatDescr.name: integraBifPortStatDescr
integraBifPortStatDescr.description: Physical network interface description. LAN1 is electrical, LAN2 and LAN3 are SFP and WAN is radio port.

integraBifPortType.name: integraBifPortType
integraBifPortType.description: The type of interface, distinguished according to the physical/link protocol(s) immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack.

integraBifPortMtu.name: integraBifPortMtu

integraBifPortSpeed.name: integraBifPortSpeed
integraBifPortSpeed.description: Link speed in bits per second.

integraBifPortPhysAddress.name: integraBifPortPhysAddress
integraBifPortPhysAddress.description: The interface's address at the protocol layer immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack. For interfaces which do not have such an address (e.g., a serial line), this object should contain an octet string of zero length.

integraBifPortAdminStatus.name: integraBifPortAdminStatus
integraBifPortAdminStatus.description: Desired state of network interfaces. Interfaces can be enabled(1), disabled(2), unknown(3) (no info received).

integraBifPortOperStatus.name: integraBifPortOperStatus
integraBifPortOperStatus.description: Actual state of interfaces. Link can be up(1), down(2) or in unknown(3) state.

integraBifPortLastChange.name: integraBifPortLastChange
integraBifPortLastChange.description: This parameter value is always 0 at the moment.

integraBifPortAutoneg.name: integraBifPortAutoneg
integraBifPortAutoneg.description: Auto-negotiation status. Unknown means no info was received.

integraBifPortSyncEthActive.name: integraBifPortSyncEthActive

integraBifPortStcIndex.name: integraBifPortStcIndex

integraBifReceivedPkts1024to1518Octets.description: Total number of received packets that were between 1024 and 1518 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

integraBifTransmittedPkts1024to1518Octet.name: integraBifTransmittedPkts1024to1518Octets
integraBifTransmittedPkts1024to1518Octet.description: Total number of transmitted packets that were between 1024 and 1518 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

integraBifIfInBroadcastPkts.name: integraBifIfInBroadcastPkts
integraBifIfInBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of received good packets that were directed to the broadcast address. Note that this does not include multicast packets.

integraBifIfOutBroadcastPkts.name: integraBifIfOutBroadcastPkts
integraBifIfOutBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of transmitted good packets that were directed to the broadcast address. Note that this does not include multicast packets.

integraBifIfInMulticastPkts.name: integraBifIfInMulticastPkts

integraBifDot3InPauseFrames.name: integraBifDot3InPauseFrames
integraBifDot3InPauseFrames.description: A count of MAC Control frames received on this interface with an opcode indicating the PAUSE operation. This counter does not increment when the interface is operating in half-duplex mode.

integraBifDot3OutPauseFrames.name: integraBifDot3OutPauseFrames
integraBifDot3OutPauseFrames.description: A count of MAC Control frames transmitted on this interface with an opcode indicating the PAUSE operation. This counter does not increment when the interface is operating in half-duplex mode.

integraBifEtherStatsUndersizePkts.name: integraBifEtherStatsUndersizePkts
integraBifEtherStatsUndersizePkts.description: The total number of packets received that were less than 64 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed.

integraBifEtherStatsFragments.name: integraBifEtherStatsFragments
integraBifEtherStatsFragments.description: The total number of packets received that were less than 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) and had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error). Note that it is entirely normal for etherStatsFragments to increment. This is because it counts both runts (which are normal occurrences due to collisions) and noise hits.

integraBifEtherStatsCRCAlignErrors.name: integraBifEtherStatsCRCAlignErrors
integraBifEtherStatsCRCAlignErrors.description: The total number of packets received that had a length (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) of between 64 and 1518 octets, inclusive, but had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error).

integraBifEtherStatsJabbers.name: integraBifEtherStatsJabbers
integraBifEtherStatsJabbers.description: The total number of packets received that were longer than 1518 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets), and had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error). Note that this definition of jabber is different than the definition in IEEE-802.3 section 8.2.1.5 (10BASE5) and section 10.3.1.4 (10BASE2). These documents define jabber as the condition where any packet exceeds 20 ms. The allowed range to detect jabber is between 20 ms and 150 ms.

integraBexecuteConfig.name: integraBexecuteConfig
integraBexecuteConfig.description: This object can only be set to 1. It initiates new running configuration applying using values, that have been set before. Setting it when no new changes are available will do nothing and return an error. GET will return 0 if there were no errors, while executing configuration or will return a bitmask, that shows which SET requests have failed. Those failed requests will be shown bit wise from LSB as follows: BIT0 radioTxMuteDuration BIT1 radioTxFrequency BIT2 radioTxPower

integraBneedStore.name: integraBneedStore
integraBneedStore.description: This object shows if there is unsaved, but executed (running) configuration. Unsaved changes will be lost after device reboot. Unsaved entities are shown bit wise, starting from LSB as follows: BIT0 Aggregation BIT1 Event log BIT2 Modem BIT3 Network BIT4 Performance BIT5 Radio BIT6 SNMP BIT7 Synchronous Ethernet BIT8 System

integraBstoreConfig.name: integraBstoreConfig
integraBstoreConfig.description: This object can only be set to 1. It initiates saving of running configuration. It will only work if there are unsaved, but executed (running) changes (configuration). Setting it when no new running configuration is available will do nothing and return an error.
